step_1: create a account in microsoft azure or login.
step_2: open azure and go to  resource groups.
step_3: create new resource group and give basic configurations.
step_4: finally click on review+create 
new resource is created successfully.
step_5: click on create virtual machine
step_6: give basic configurations.
step_7: give size of ram and cpu.
step_8: give vm image as windows datacentre.
step_9: click on review+create
step_10: run it
step_11: click on connect and select rdp file
step_12: download rdp file and open it
